Governor Bala Mohammed’s brother, Adamu Mohammed who was kidnapped on March 25 by unknown gunmen has regained freedom. Adamu was abducted at a local shop by the gunmen who struck without being stopped. Chief of Staff to the Bauchi governor, Ladan Salihu confirmed the development by sharing a video of Mr Mohammed’s reunion with his family on Tuesday evening. He wrote; Thanks be to God. The Representative of Bauchi, elder brother to Governor Bala Mohammed released by kidnappers… moments ago in Bauchi. Hausa: May Allah save us from Adamu. This Mohammed from hannon those who have been kidnapped by him. Alhamdulillah. Source For Mohammed Abubakar the Governor of Bauchi State, this must be one of the longest nights of his life. Tomorrow, Monday, 25 March 2019, the court is likely to rule on whether or not the Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC, can proceed with collation of the result of Tafawa Balewa… March 25, 2019 In "Social Media Feeds" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Presidential candidate of the People’s Democratic Party and former Vice President, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar has congratulated the governor-elect of Bauchi State, Bala Mohammed for his victory at the just concluded governorship election in the state. Atiku who described his victory as “deeply satisfying,”… March 27, 2019 In "Politics" Court Orders EFCC To Release Bala Mohammed On Bail The candidate of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), Bala Mohammed, has won the supplementary election in Bauchi State. Returning Officer Professor Kyari Mohammed made the announcement on Sunday, a day after the exercise took place in the state. According to him,… March 24, 2019 In "Top Stories"